00:14:00.096 --> 00:14:03.066 A:middle
Then the screen is going to
pass it down to all the windows

00:14:03.066 --> 00:14:06.106 A:middle
that are on that screen and then
the window is going to pass it

00:14:06.106 --> 00:14:08.426 A:middle
to its root view
controller to its view,

00:14:08.426 --> 00:14:10.146 A:middle
then down to its
subview controllers

00:14:10.146 --> 00:14:11.806 A:middle
and subviews and so on.

00:14:12.856 --> 00:14:16.596 A:middle
Now each stop along the way
here is a class that conforms

00:14:16.596 --> 00:14:20.076 A:middle
to UITraitEnvironment and the
UITraitEnvironment has a key

00:14:20.076 --> 00:14:22.816 A:middle
method called
traitCollectionDidChange.

00:14:23.416 --> 00:14:24.826 A:middle
So at each stop along the way

00:14:24.826 --> 00:14:26.326 A:middle
as this trait collection
is getting propagated

00:14:26.326 --> 00:14:28.716 A:middle
down it's going to call
traitCollectionDidChange.

00:14:29.106 --> 00:14:31.966 A:middle
This is where you as
developers are going to override

00:14:32.176 --> 00:14:34.066 A:middle
and make your applications
adaptive.

00:14:34.446 --> 00:14:36.526 A:middle
So traitCollectionDidChange
is the key method here.

00:14:37.696 --> 00:14:40.416 A:middle
And you're almost exclusively
going to override this

00:14:40.536 --> 00:14:42.676 A:middle
at the view controller
and the view level.

